"I want to step in here with a suggestion. To make things clearer and fairer for contributors, I have proposed a 1-week "to be deleted" period when a page is flagged. During that time, the notice will include a reason so the page creator (or anyone else) can update it and resolve the issue. If no action is taken in that timeframe, the deletion will proceed.  
------
This should help avoid misunderstandings and ensure contributors feel they have a chance to fix things while still keeping the wiki organized and useful. Tupper - VRC Team 18:52, 18 August 2025 (UTC)"

I Do agree with the new policy, I would personally suggest 10 days rather then 7 days as I'm not aware of any downsides outside of byte data consumption (please let me know otherwise).
