== Implementation rule of Colours on user signatures ==

I also request new rule implementation on Signatures, Currently any user can set whatever they like (which I don't hold anything agaisnt that) But I do hold color modification of the username display as a Major negative.
-----
Lets look the (my) known examples, Myself I have a red username which indicates I don't have a page, A user like @[[User:Hackebein|hackebein]] for example has a blue name, indicating they have a page, @[[User:Trixxedheart|trixxedheart]] has a Purple name, On my first experience seeing this I instantly thought they were a mod (this was before reviewing any pages about Wiki maintainer/team members).

I've never seen this type of colored name, I support the usage of siginitures, but Not color modifiations to the name as it can potetionally mislead peoples thoughts on who/what that users role is without reviewing the team members themselfs. [[User:Usr 1a5319fb-f3a7-4ee9-8ed3-83c96116b509|Usr 1a5319fb-f3a7-4ee9-8ed3-83c96116b509]] ([[User talk:Usr 1a5319fb-f3a7-4ee9-8ed3-83c96116b509|talk]]) 20:31, 18 August 2025 (UTC)